From 755544d32245dbb042574dbc7c9444227f31b4c0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Zhang, Xiaolin" <xiaolin.zhang@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Apr 2026 14:37:48 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] refactor(dflash): decouple Qwen3-Omni DFlash from Qwen3.5
 dependency

Qwen3-Omni DFlash speculative decoding previously reused the Qwen3.5
draft model builders (create_qwen3_5_dflash_combined_draft_model, etc.)
by constructing a Qwen3_5Config compatibility shim from QWen3OmniConfig.
This created an unnecessary cross-model dependency where the Omni sample
included Qwen3.5 headers and relied on Qwen3.5 types.

This commit introduces Omni-native DFlash draft model builder functions
that are fully independent of any Qwen3.5 code:

  - create_qwen3_omni_dflash_combined_draft_model()
    Merges embed_tokens + DFlash draft layers + lm_head into a single
    graph.  Handles Qwen3-Omni's tie_word_embeddings quirk (safetensors
    stores a separate lm_head.weight that must not overwrite the tied
    embed_tokens binding).

  - create_qwen3_omni_dflash_context_kv_model()
    Computes fc + RMSNorm + K,V projections + KNorm + RoPE for all draft
    layers.  Used for context KV preprocessing on newly-accepted tokens.

  - create_qwen3_omni_dflash_step_model()
    Lightweight draft step: embed -> attention (with pre-computed context
    KV) -> MLP -> lm_head.  Skips fc + context KV computation entirely.

Changes per file:

  modeling_qwen3_omni_text.cpp (+214 lines):
    - Added #include for dflash_draft.hpp
    - Implemented the 3 new Omni-specific DFlash builder functions
    - Each function takes Qwen3OmniConfig directly (no Qwen3_5Config shim)

  modeling_qwen3_omni.hpp (+43 lines):
    - Forward declaration of DFlashDraftConfig
    - Declared the 3 new builder functions with full doxygen comments

  modeling_qwen3_omni_dflash.cpp (-17 lines):
    - Removed #include of qwen3_5 headers (modeling_qwen3_5_text.hpp,
      processing_qwen3_5.hpp)
    - Removed Qwen3_5Config compat_cfg construction
    - Replaced call to create_qwen3_5_dflash_combined_draft_model with
      create_qwen3_omni_dflash_combined_draft_model

The Qwen3.5 DFlash functions remain unchanged and continue to work
independently for Qwen3.5 models.  The lm_head tie_word_embeddings
bugfix in modeling_qwen3_5_text.cpp (commit 2df78ece) is preserved
as a standalone general improvement.
